          "type": "category",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Materials & craftsmanship",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "open_first_question": false,
            "question_1": "What materials do you use?",
            "answer_1": "<p>WRYDECO focuses on solid natural wood selected for grain, form, and suitability for the design. The product page or project proposal identifies the material and finish specified for your piece.</p>",
            "question_2": "Will my piece look exactly like the photograph?",
            "answer_2": "<p>Its design language will be consistent, but no two pieces of natural wood share identical grain, tone, knots, or edge character. Those differences make each work singular.</p>",
            "question_3": "How is the furniture made?",
            "answer_3": "<p>Skilled artisans shape, join, finish, and inspect each work with close attention to the wood's natural form. The process balances sculptural expression with everyday function and long-term use.</p>"
          }
        },
